@author Kindynos
 @title The contract that deploys and controls IndexFunds.

@notice retrieves the address of the IndexFund, if it exists.
 @param _tokenArray the array of addresses that make the fund.
@notice returns the total amount of different Index Funds.
@notice gets the codeHash of the IndexFund base contract.

devdoc.author: Kindynos

claimOwnership().details: If the address has been proposed, it can accept the ownership, Can only be called by the current proposed owner.

params._proportionsArray: The amounts of the respective tokens that represent a (1) unit of the Fund Token
params._tokenArray: The token addresses that make the fund.
the array of addresses that make the fund.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proposeOwner(address).details: Proposes a new owner of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._newVaults: The addresses of the new vaults.
params._tokenArray: The token addresses that make the fund.

params._tokenArray: The token addresses that make the fund.

devdoc.title: The contract that deploys and controls IndexFunds.

allFundsLength().notice: returns the total amount of different Index Funds.

fundCodeHash().notice: gets the codeHash of the IndexFund base contract.

getFund(address[]).notice: retrieves the address of the IndexFund, if it exists.

setFeeTo(address).notice: Sets the address that receives the dev Fees if activated.

setInvestingNumerator(address[],uint256).notice: Modify amount that is invested from an IndexFund
